EasyOCRTesseractmacOS VisionRapidOCR <p>Best for multi-language documents with accuracy requirements.</p> <pre><code>{
  "ocr": {
    "backend": "easyocr",
    "use_gpu": true,
    "language": "en"
  }
}
</code></pre> <ul> <li>GPU Support: Yes (CUDA)</li> <li>Languages: 80+</li> <li>Note: May have initialization issues on some systems</li> </ul> <p>Classic, reliable OCR engine for simple documents.</p> <pre><code>{
  "ocr": {
    "backend": "tesseract",
    "language": "eng"
  }
}
</code></pre> <ul> <li>GPU Support: No</li> <li>Languages: 100+</li> <li>Requires: Tesseract installed on system</li> </ul> <p>Native macOS OCR using Apple's Vision framework.</p> <pre><code>{
  "ocr": {
    "backend": "ocrmac",
    "language": "en"
  }
}
</code></pre> <ul> <li>GPU Support: Uses Apple Neural Engine</li> <li>Requires: macOS 10.15+</li> <li>Language codes: Duckling accepts short codes like <code>en</code>, <code>de</code>, <code>fr</code> and will normalize them to Vision locale tags (for example <code>en-US</code>) during conversion.</li> </ul> <p>Fast, lightweight OCR using ONNX runtime.</p> <pre><code>{
  "ocr": {
    "backend": "rapidocr",
    "language": "en"
  }
}
</code></pre> <ul> <li>GPU Support: No</li> <li>Languages: Limited</li> </ul>

Accurate ModeFast Mode <pre><code>{
  "tables": {
    "enabled": true,
    "mode": "accurate",
    "do_cell_matching": true
  }
}
</code></pre> <ul> <li>Higher precision table detection</li> <li>Better cell boundary recognition</li> <li>Slower processing</li> <li>Recommended for complex tables</li> </ul> <pre><code>{
  "tables": {
    "enabled": true,
    "mode": "fast",
    "do_cell_matching": false
  }
}
</code></pre> <ul> <li>Faster processing</li> <li>Good for simple tables</li> <li>May miss complex structures</li> </ul>

